'''César Lecat baron de Bazancourt''' (1810–1865) was a French military historian, director of the library of [[Château de Compiègne|Compiègne]] under [[Louis-Philippe of France|Louis Philippe]].
He was born in Paris and was appointed official [[Historiography|historiographer]] by [[Napoleon III of France|Napoleon III]], whom he accompanied during several campaigns. The results of these [[Military campaign|expedition]]s appeared in his works on ''L'Expédition de Crimée jusqu'à la prise de Sébastopol, chronique de la [[Crimean War|guerre d'Orient]]'' (1856); ''La campagne d'Italie de 1859, chronique de la guerre'' (1859); and ''Les expéditions de Chine et de Cochinchine'' (two volumes, 1861–62).
